          id: "news-1",
          title: "From Courts to the Stages of the World",
          source: "Super Esportes (03/09/2018)",
          date: "September 3, 2018",
          summary: "After reaching the Brazilian National handball selection as an elite player, Nilton Cruz pursued his dream of making music and was nominated for the Latin Grammy.",
          content: [
            "Sport and the acoustic guitar were the two passions of a boy born in Belo Horizonte in the early 1960s. After playing for Ginástico, Nilton Cruz reached the Brazilian National Team and was known as 'Canhão' (Handball Cannon). Time passed and the athlete became Nil Lus, a prolific singer and songwriter, nominated for the Latin Grammy.",
            "This story begins in the Nova Vista neighborhood, where he was raised. Since childhood, he wanted to play the piano. His mother Raimunda gave him an old acoustic guitar on his 10th birthday. He learned by training day and night.",
            "He represented Brazil internationally in pre-olympic and panamerican tournaments. However, during a tournament in Canada, he made the decision to stay in North America to follow his musical call. He eventually caught the attention of a producer who brought him to Europe.",
            "His career skyrocketed. He went on to release multiple albums, perform twice at the prestigious Montreux Jazz Festival, and travel through America, Asia, and Europe playing in over 45 countries."
          ]
        },
        {
          id: "news-2",
          title: "Alma Feminina Show Launches National Tour at Teatro Bradesco",
          source: "Agenda BH",
          date: "October 05, 2017",
          summary: "Back in his hometown, Nil Lus presents a special show for his 15th career album, reflecting on the historical, social, and mystical power of women.",
          content: [
            "Poet and songwriter Nil Lus presents his new show 'Alma Feminina', delivering a highly delicate vision of women's historical and political role in society.",
            "Under the musical direction of Celso Rangel and technical production by Ricardo Kozlowscky, the show opens its national and international tour with special guest stars at Teatro Bradesco in Belo Horizonte.",
            "“I approach all aspects of her journey, from childhood, adolescence, mother, lover, worker, executive, grandmother... With a sacred focus on the miracle of life,” says Nil."
          ]
        },
        {
          id: "news-3",
          title: "Ambassador of Brazilian Music Excellence in Europe",
          source: "Brasil Flash TV (01/09/2020)",
          date: "September 1, 2020",
          summary: "Praised by international critics and colleagues, Nil Lus is recognized as a globetrotter of sounds, fusing Latin grooves with modern British pop.",
          content: [
            "Nil Lus is the author of over a thousand songs and has recorded 15 albums between Europe and Brazil. For American critic Johnny Marty, Nil Lus is 'The Sting of Brazil' because of his jazz-infused and literary style.",
            "He is currently recording a soundtrack for a German feature film and preparing a tetralogy of esoteric thriller books, showing an unstoppable creative energy."
          ]
        }
